<para id="element-51">We see that total time of flight is twice the time projectile takes to reach the maximum height. It means that projectile takes equal times in "up" and "down"  motion. In other words, time of ascent equals time of descent.   
</para>

<example id="example-1">
<para id="element-52"><term>Problem : </term> A ball is thrown upwards with a speed of 10 m/s making an angle 30° with horizontal and returning to ground on same horizontal level. Find (i) time of flight and (ii) and time to reach the maximum height 
</para>

<para id="element-53"> <term>Solution : </term> Here, component of initial velocity in vertical direction is : 
</para>
